&lt;h2&gt;


Introduction
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When I joined the GitHub Copilot CLI Challenge, I didn‚Äôt want to build just another command-line tool.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I wanted to build something that feels like a real cybersecurity utility ‚Äî something that provides actual visibility into what‚Äôs happening inside your system.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So I built &lt;strong&gt;Sentinel AI&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sentinel AI is a production-ready cybersecurity CLI built with Python and accelerated using GitHub Copilot CLI. It analyzes active network connections, classifies risk levels using structured scoring, and delivers actionable intelligence directly from the terminal.&lt;/p&gt;




&lt;h2&gt;


What is Sentinel AI?
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sentinel AI is a modular Python-based CLI tool that:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitors active network connections&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detects suspicious indicators&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Classifies risk levels using a numeric scoring system (0‚Äì100)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provides summarized security intelligence reports&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Displays structured system information&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is designed to feel like a lightweight, terminal-based Security Operations Center (SOC).&lt;/p&gt;




&lt;h2&gt;


Why I Built This
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Modern systems constantly open and close network connections. As developers, we install packages, run services, connect to APIs, and open ports ‚Äî often without inspecting what‚Äôs actually happening underneath.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I wanted a tool that:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Makes invisible network activity visible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adds intelligent classification instead of raw output&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Feels structured and professional&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Is fast and lightweight&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sentinel AI brings clarity and measurable risk assessment into the terminal.&lt;/p&gt;




&lt;h2&gt;


